				<text>8.1.4.2 (not in quiz): Solving three equations in three unknowns</text>
		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Use Cramer's rule to find the solution of the system: <br> <br> \[ {@eqns[1]@}\ =\ {@bmat[1,1]@} , \] \[ {@eqns[2]@}\ =\ {@bmat[2,1]@} , \] \[ {@eqns[3]@}\ =\ {@bmat[3,1]@} , \] <br> \(x=\) [[input:ans1]]&nbsp;[[validation:ans1]]<br> \(y=\) [[input:ans2]]&nbsp;[[validation:ans2]]<br> \(z=\) [[input:ans3]]&nbsp;[[validation:ans3]]<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;[[feedback:Result]]</p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>Cramer's rule states that \(x = \frac{\Delta_{x}}{\Delta}\) where \(\Delta\) is the determinant of the matrix and \(\Delta_{x}\) is the determinant of the matrix with the x column replaced by the numbers on the right hand side of
the equations and similarly \(y = \frac{\Delta_{y}}{\Delta}\) and \(z = \frac{\Delta_{z}}{\Delta}\). <br>
</p><p></p>
<p>Therefore for the system, <br> \[{@eqns[1]@}\ =\ {@bmat[1,1]@} , \] \[ {@eqns[2]@}\ =\ {@bmat[2,1]@} , \] \[ {@eqns[3]@}\ =\ {@bmat[3,1]@} , \]<br> \[ \Delta = \det{@Amat@}={@D@},\]<br> \[\Delta_{x} = \det{@Amatx@}={@Dx@},\]<br> \[\Delta_{y} = \det{@Amaty@}={@Dy@},\]
    and<br> \[\Delta_{z} = \det{@Amatz@}={@Dz@},\]</p>
<p>where the notation \(\det A = |A|\) is the determinant of a matrix \(A\).&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p><br> Hence, \[x=\frac{@Dx@}{@D@} = {@Dx/D@},\] <br> </p>
<p>\[y=\frac{@Dy@}{@D@} = {@Dy/D@},\]&nbsp; and</p>
<p> \[z=\frac{@Dz@}{@D@} = {@Dz/D@}.\]</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
